<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-18961] Record commit timestamp - fix data loss when dropping and recreating a column</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-18961</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Drop column transformation is replayed with the current timestamp so the column appears to be dropped when the node starts regardless of its real drop time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As a solution to this problem I propose recording the timestamp of the transformation, guaranteeing that it is always greater than a timestamp of any previously committed transformation. Such timestamp is passed to the execute method of the transformation so that the transformation code can make use of it, increasing its &quot;purity&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
